-- Brewin Dolphin Names Nicol CEO; Matheson Steps Down as Chairman
-- B y   E d w a r d   E v a n s
-- 2013-03-21T07:28:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-21/brewin-dolphin-names-nicol-ceo-matheson-steps-down-as-chairman.html
Brewin Dolphin Holdings Plc (BRW)  named
former  Morgan Stanley (MS)  executive David Nicol chief executive
officer after Jamie Matheson s tepped down after eight years as
executive chairman.  Simon Miller will become non-executive chairman and Stephen Ford will become executive director, responsible for fund
investment management, the London-based stockbroker and money
manager said in a statement today. Chief Operating Officer Henry Algeo and directors Ben Speke and Sarah Soar are also stepping
down.  Matheson “will be working with David Nicol and the
management team to ensure a smooth transition to the new
leadership, while also being able to devote more time to his
other business and charitable interests,” the company said.  The firm is overhauling the board after Matheson initiated
a strategic review in 2011 aimed at widening the company’s
margins.  To contact the reporter on this story:
